WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Bobarr' is a Workbench game where you have to move all the bars
that are shown on the 7 by 7 spaces board. The game is based on
the usual 'Sliding-bars' puzzles, but Bobarr offers a variation:
in addition to horizontal and vertical bars, there are also
diagonal bars that have to be moved... and each type of bar can be
moved in the directions its shape represent (a horizontal bar can
move to the left or right, a vertical bar can move up or down and
a diagonal bar can move diagonally up or down, depending on which
"way" it is placed)... if the empty space is located in line and
next to that bar.

  To add some confusion to the game, any bar located at the edge
of the board can move to the other side... if, of course, the
empty space is on the other side and in line with that bar.

  As a bar is moved, its former position is then indicated by a
coloured rectangular shape, if such a shape was not already at
that position. When all bars have been moved, the game is
completed... ideally, the fewest moves that are taken to complete
a game, the better it is...

  Have fun!

